p:
Five friends bought a gift for $\text{dollar} 120$. The first friend contributed half of the sum of the amounts contributed by the other four; 
the second friend contributed one-third of the sum of the amounts contributed by the other four; 
the third friend contributed one-fourth of the sum of the amounts contributed by the other four; 
and the fourth friend contributed one-fifth of the sum of the amounts contributed by the other four. How much did the fifth friend contribute?
$\textbf{(A) }\text{dollar} 48\qquad \textbf{(B) }\text{dollar} 50\qquad \textbf{(C) }\text{dollar} 52.55\qquad \textbf{(D) }\text{dollar} 55\qquad \textbf{(E) }\text{dollar} 60$
